Simple version

#simple version

#raw data
ggplot(data2, aes(x=strain, y=size)) +
  geom_jitter() +
  stat_summary(fun=mean, geom="crossbar", colour = "red", position=position_dodge(width=0.5))

#boxplot
ggplot(data2, aes(x=strain, y=size)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  stat_summary(fun=mean, geom="point", position=position_dodge(width=0.5))

#barplot
ggplot(data2.5_stat, aes(x=strain, y=mean)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", fill = "steelblue")  

#histogram
ggplot(data2, aes(x=size, fill=strain)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth=50, alpha=.5, position="identity")  

#density plot
ggplot(data2, aes(x=size, fill=strain)) +
  geom_density(alpha=.5) 

#violin plot
ggplot(data2, aes(x=strain, y=size, fill=strain)) +
  geom_violin() 

#Line plot
ggplot(data2.5_stat, aes(x=strain, y=mean)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(aes(group=1)) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=mean-sd, ymax=mean+sd), width=.2)

#Scatter plot
ggplot(data3, aes(x=cellcycle, y=size))+
  geom_point()

##Trend lines
ggplot(data3, aes(x=cellcycle, y=size))+
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = lm)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

Example 1:

#original example
ggplot(data2, aes(x=strain, y=size)) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape=NA) 

#modified version
ggplot(data2, aes(x=strain, y=size, fill = strain)) +
  #note:raw data
  geom_jitter(shape = 1, height = 0, color="#BDC0BA", size = 2, width = 0.3) +
  #note:box plots
  geom_boxplot(outlier.color = "darkred", outlier.shape = 4) +
  
  #note:add necessary stats
  stat_summary(fun = "mean", geom = "point", shape = 21, size = 3, fill = "white") +
  #note:change sample names on X-axis
  scale_x_discrete(labels=c("haploids","diploids","triploids", "tetraploids")) +
  #note:change box colors
  scale_fill_manual(values=c("#B28FCE", "#81C7D4","#58B2DC","#66327C")) +
  #note:change backgroup colors
  theme_bw() +
  #note:change X-axis labels
  theme(axis.title.x = element_text(face="bold", colour="grey", size=16),
        axis.text.x  = element_text(size=12),
  #note:change Y-axis labels
        axis.title.y = element_text(face="bold", colour="grey", size=16),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size=12)) +
  #note:change Y-axis scale
  ylim(0,2100) +
  #note:change axis labels
  ylab("size (a.u.)") +  
  xlab("") +
  #note:change Y-axis
  labs(title = "Ploidy effects")

Example 2:

#original example
ggplot(data3, aes(x=cellcycle, y=size))+
  geom_point()

#modified version

data3_pick <- read.csv("size3pick.csv", header = TRUE)
data3_pick2 <- read.csv("size3pick2.csv", header = TRUE)

ggplot()+
  geom_point(data=data3, 
             aes(x=cellcycle, y=size), shape = 1, size = 3, alpha = 0.7, color= "#0D5661") +
  geom_point(data=data3_pick, 
             aes(x=cellcycle, y=size), shape = 15, size = 3, alpha = 0.5, color= "#DB4D6D") +
  geom_point(data=data3_pick2, 
             aes(x=cellcycle, y=size), shape = 18, size = 5, alpha = 1, color= "#572A3F") +
  geom_label_repel(data=subset(data3, cellcycle > 1), 
                   aes(x=cellcycle, y=size, label = strain)) +
  theme_classic() +
  #note:change axis labels
  ylab("size (a.u.)") +  
  xlab(" G1/G2 ratio") +
  #note:change Y-axis
  labs(title = "cell cycle effects")

Example 3:

#original example
ggplot(data4, aes(x=var, y=strain, fill=foldchange))+
  geom_tile(color = "grey80") +
  scale_fill_gradient2(
    low = "steelblue", 
    high = "red", 
    midpoint = 1, limits = c(0.01,3)) 

#modified version
data4$strain <- factor(data4$strain, levels = unique(rev(data4$strain)))
ggplot(data4, aes(x=var, y=strain, fill=foldchange))+
  geom_tile(color = "grey80") +
  scale_fill_gradient2(
    low = "#FBE251", 
    high = "#77428D", 
    midpoint = 1, limits = c(0,3))  +
   theme_bw() +
  scale_x_discrete(labels = c("G1/G2","Size"))+
  theme( 
    axis.title.x = element_text(size=20),
    axis.text.x  = element_text(angle=90, vjust=0.5,size=15),
    axis.title.y = element_text(size=15),
    axis.text.y  = element_text(face = "italic",size=12)
    ) +
  xlab("") +
  guides(fill = guide_colorbar(title = " Fold \n change \n") )
